title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Find the top 100 customers who have placed large-volume orders, where a large order is defined as an order whose total quantity exceeds 300. For each qualifying order, return the customer name, customer key, order key, order date, total price, and the total quantity of the order. Sort by total price desc. Output the results to a textfile.SQL_QUERY:

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => (r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int], r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Double])
(a: (Int, Double), b: (Int, Double)) => (a._1, a._2 + b._2)
(r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => (r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int], (r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Int], r.getField(2), r.getField(3).asInstanceOf[Double]))
(t: ((Int, Double), (Int, (Int, Any, Double)))) => { val qty = t._1._2; val o = t._2; val orderkey = o._1; val oc = o._2._1; val od = o._2._2; val price = o._2._3; (oc, (orderkey, od, price, qty)) }
(r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => (r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int], r.getField(1).toString)

(t: ((Int, (Int, Any, Double, Double)), (Int, String))) => { val custname = t._2._2; val custkey = t._2._1; val orderinfo = t._1._2; val orderkey = orderinfo._1; val orderdate = orderinfo._2; val price = orderinfo._3; val qty = orderinfo._4; (price, (custname, custkey, orderkey, orderdate, price, qty)) }
(t: (Double, (String, Int, Int, Any, Double, Double))) => List(t)
(a: List[(Double, (String, Int, Int, Any, Double, Double))], b: List[(Double, (String, Int, Int, Any, Double, Double))]) => (a ++ b).take(100)
(lst: List[(Double, (String, Int, Int, Any, Double, Double))]) => lst
(t: (Double, (String, Int, Int, Any, Double, Double))) => { val d = t._2; s"${d._1} | ${d._2} | ${d._3} | ${d._4} | ${d._5} | ${d._6}" }
